 fields of early modern art production and aesthetic theory that can be asked about the artistic use of the natural material stone and its imitation in painting. This collection presents over 40 sources with commentaries from the ancient period up to the 18th century that can be used to reconstruct the written discourse on stone – marble, porphyry, and precious stones – and the semanticization of this material.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aKunst. 4aMalerei. 4aMaterial. 4aStein. 7aART / Techniques / General.2bisacsh  aStone.  aart.  amaterial.  apainting.1 aArnulf, Arwed, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAugart, Isabella, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBadura, Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeate Lohff, Johanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBiermann, Veronica, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlum, Gerd, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrahms, Iris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBucklow, Spike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBuss, Franca, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCordez, Philippe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFelfe, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFliege, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrede, Dorothea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGastel, Joris van, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHermann Vennebusch, Jochen, econtributor.4ctb4https